Dollarhide — Argued January 21, Hanna — Submitted on record and briefs January 23, STATE OF OREGON, Respondent, v. JAMES MICHAEL DOLLARHIDE, Appellant. 464 P.2d 721 Gary D. Babcock, Public Defender, Salem, argued the cause and filed the brief for appellant. G. Dwyer Wilson, Deputy District Attorney, Hillsboro, argued the cause for respondent. With him on the brief was Ray D. Robinett, District Attorney, Hillsboro.
